  <!-- Steps -->
<h2 class ="ex2"> Step 1</h2>
<p class="ex1">Mix 60ml warm milk, 3g instant coffee and 3g cocoa powder together.</p>

<h2 class ="ex2"> Step 2</h2>
<p class="ex1">In another bowl mix 3 egg yolks, 15g granulated sugar, 1/4 tsp of salt and 30 ml corn oil together. Then put in the coffee mixture.</p>

<h2 class ="ex2"> Step 3</h2>
<p class="ex1">Mix well 60g cake flour, 2g baking powder into the coffee mixture. </p>

<h2 class ="ex2"> Step 4</h2>
<p class="ex1">Whip 3 egg white until soft peaks form(tips curl), while whipping, gradually add in 30g granulated sugar. </p>

<h2 class ="ex2"> Step 5</h2>
<p class="ex1">Mix egg white paste well with coffee paste in several times.</p>

<h2 class ="ex2"> Step 6</h2>
<p class="ex1">Put the well combined paste in cake mold, bake at 165Â°C degrees for 40-45 minutes. </p>

<h2 class ="ex2"> Step 7</h2>
<p class="ex1">While waiting, mix 100g mascarpone cheese and 30g granulated sugar. Then add 150g heavy milk with 1 tsp of vanilla extract. Whip the cream until soft peaks form. </p>

<h2 class ="ex2"> Step 8</h2>
<p class="ex1">Take the cake out of mold, circle the cake with plastic film. Pour in mascarpone cream, you can add cocoa powder on top to decorate. </p>

<h2 class ="ex2"> Step 9</h2>
<p class="ex1">Take out the plastic film and enjoy your cake.</p>

